246
00:22:57.640 --> 00:23:02.000
Yoon Ji Soo came out. The others have also been released with a warning.

247
00:23:15.980 --> 00:23:18.210
<i>May, 1994</i>

248
00:23:18.210 --> 00:23:21.100
What are you going to do about our Ji Soo?

249
00:23:21.100 --> 00:23:22.790
What do you want me to do about it?

250
00:23:22.790 --> 00:23:24.980
Are you asking because you don't know?

251
00:23:25.800 --> 00:23:29.650
You know that she likes you, Hyung.

252
00:23:29.650 --> 00:23:34.650
Why won't you just tell her if you like her or not?

253
00:23:34.650 --> 00:23:36.550
Yeong Woo,

254
00:23:37.800 --> 00:23:39.020
actually, I'm dating Ji Soo—

255
00:23:39.020 --> 00:23:42.350
She keeps following you around like a zombie.

256
00:23:42.350 --> 00:23:45.220
Don't you even feel bad for her?

257
00:23:45.220 --> 00:23:46.810
Why are you being like this?

258
00:23:46.810 --> 00:23:48.300
What did I do?

259
00:23:48.300 --> 00:23:53.340
If I draw boundaries with Ji Soo, what are you going to do?

260
00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:56.480
What do you mean, what will I do?

261
00:23:56.480 --> 00:24:00.580
But she doesn't look at me.

262
00:24:00.580 --> 00:24:06.830
She doesn't look behind her or to her side but keeps looking only to the front.

263
00:24:06.830 --> 00:24:12.780
That girl is as steadfast as Joan of Arc.

264
00:24:57.970 --> 00:24:59.980
What is this?

265
00:24:59.980 --> 00:25:04.250
Is it something like Pandora's box?

266
00:25:06.060 --> 00:25:09.100
I hope the negotiation goes well.

267
00:25:09.100 --> 00:25:13.190
<i>What about you? Are you thinking of reinstatement?</i>

268
00:25:13.190 --> 00:25:15.410
I found a job.

269
00:25:15.410 --> 00:25:17.650
<i>Really? That's good.</i>

270
00:25:17.650 --> 00:25:20.670
<i>Not as a contract worker, but a full-time employee, right?</i>

271
00:25:21.520 --> 00:25:23.270
<i>Ocean Music School</i>

272
00:25:23.270 --> 00:25:27.530
You said you would come yesterday, how could you change the meeting on the same day?

273
00:25:27.530 --> 00:25:30.940
I'm sorry. A situation came up for me yesterday.

274
00:25:30.940 --> 00:25:32.820
We can't overlook things because of personal situations.

275
00:25:32.820 --> 00:25:36.740
This isn't a place where we deal with children, we deal with their mothers.

276
00:25:36.740 --> 00:25:40.770
If you come even a minute late or teach them for a minute less, we get calls from the mothers immediately.

277
00:25:40.770 --> 00:25:42.690
And they request schedule changes all the time.

278
00:25:42.690 --> 00:25:44.390
Yes, I will be careful of that.

279
00:25:44.390 --> 00:25:49.500
Also, you can never tell the mothers that you dropped out of college.

280
00:25:49.500 --> 00:25:51.010
Yes.

281
00:25:51.010 --> 00:25:54.600
You said you would organize and clean the academy as well.

282
00:25:54.600 --> 00:25:58.220
- Is that right?
 - Yes. I'll work hard.

283
00:25:59.150 --> 00:26:01.590
<i>Hywong Swong Mart Reinstatement Applicants List</i>

284
00:26:01.590 --> 00:26:03.820
<i>Kim Ji Seon, Kim Seon Woo, Kim Na Yeong, Kim Jin Rae, Kim Sin Hee...</i>

285
00:26:05.610 --> 00:26:07.350
<i>Yoon Jin Seo, Yoon Ji Seong, Yoon Ji Yoon, Yoon Ji Yeon...</i>

286
00:26:07.350 --> 00:26:09.650
<i>Yoon Na Jeong, Yoon Na Seon, Yoon Jeong Yoon, Yoon Jin Seo...</i>

287
00:26:28.490 --> 00:26:31.750
I saw that you didn't apply for reinstatement.

288
00:26:31.750 --> 00:26:33.620
No.

289
00:26:33.620 --> 00:26:36.000
Is it because you're uncomfortable with me?

290
00:26:37.090 --> 00:26:39.200
I found a different part-time job.

291
00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:44.050
I think you need a stable job. Why did you make that decision?

292
00:26:44.050 --> 00:26:45.750
A permanent position.

293
00:26:46.550 --> 00:26:49.800
Isn't that what you were protesting for?

294
00:26:49.800 --> 00:26:52.890
It's the table that the unnis set.

295
00:26:52.890 --> 00:26:57.320
All I did was bring water. I don't have the right to lay my spoon on that table.

296
00:26:59.370 --> 00:27:05.380
Those are spots that should go to people who staked their lives to protest from start to finish.

297
00:27:06.750 --> 00:27:11.460
I had given up in the middle, using the excuse that I had to make a living.

298
00:27:11.460 --> 00:27:13.230
Then other than those positions.

299
00:27:13.230 --> 00:27:16.250
Do you have any thoughts of doing other work, such as a desk job?

300
00:27:16.250 --> 00:27:20.560
Did you give this offer to the others as well?

301
00:27:20.560 --> 00:27:21.810
No.

302
00:27:21.810 --> 00:27:23.260
Then isn't this a corrupt offer of employment?

303
00:27:23.260 --> 00:27:26.260
It's not illegal for me to hire people I want to work in my company.

304
00:27:26.260 --> 00:27:29.540
Bringing in an incompetent person will be a problem.

305
00:27:29.540 --> 00:27:33.030
What would someone who majored in piano do there?

306
00:27:33.030 --> 00:27:36.800
I didn't even graduate from college, so in reality, I'm just a high school graduate.

307
00:27:38.980 --> 00:27:41.470
Sunbae,

308
00:27:41.470 --> 00:27:46.600
I don't have anything, and I don't have much to show for my life.

309
00:27:47.440 --> 00:27:53.240
But that was probably why my heart was lighter.

310
00:27:54.500 --> 00:27:58.360
I was busy just thinking about the future,

311
00:27:58.360 --> 00:28:03.010
so I didn't have the time nor the need to reminisce on memories.

312
00:28:03.010 --> 00:28:08.990
But after meeting you, my heart has become heavy again.

313
00:28:10.240 --> 00:28:16.660
I keep looking behind me, so my footsteps become slower.

314
00:28:20.250 --> 00:28:23.960
I wanted to leave those times that were pretty like flowers, just as they were.

315
00:28:26.040 --> 00:28:30.390
But it feels like the sunbae who has changed is trampling all over those flowers, so I'm angry.

316
00:28:30.390 --> 00:28:33.250
Then you shouldn't have left.

317
00:28:36.070 --> 00:28:38.920
How can separation be pretty?

318
00:28:41.630 --> 00:28:43.780
I still

319
00:28:46.220 --> 00:28:50.230
don't understand why you left like that.

320
00:29:01.970 --> 00:29:07.160
When sharing my pain, for me, it doesn't get halved, but rather becomes twice as painful.

321
00:29:09.430 --> 00:29:12.730
Because I have to see the person I love being in pain.

322
00:29:14.210 --> 00:29:18.930
Is there a bigger pain than separation from someone you love?

323
00:29:21.160 --> 00:29:26.300
Ji Soo, I also don't reminisce about memories

324
00:29:26.300 --> 00:29:30.050
because you were never just a memory to me.

325
00:29:32.520 --> 00:29:35.700
You were like a heavy rock weighing down my heart,

326
00:29:36.970 --> 00:29:40.770
a fishbone stuck in my throat. How can that become a memory?

327
00:29:45.630 --> 00:29:48.290
Just leave it as a memory.

328
00:29:50.390 --> 00:29:56.630
Just remember the good memories, I will do the same.

329
00:30:33.410 --> 00:30:36.700
♫ Your ♫

330
00:30:36.700 --> 00:30:40.450
<i>June, 1994</i> 
 ♫ silence ♫

331
00:30:40.450 --> 00:30:46.790
♫ has dried out my lips ♫

332
00:30:46.790 --> 00:30:53.140
♫ As you turn away, I tell you ♫

333
00:30:53.140 --> 00:30:59.010
♫ Goodbye, goodbye ♫

334
00:31:08.920 --> 00:31:11.210
In the eyes of a music major, I'm pretty good, right?

335
00:31:11.210 --> 00:31:13.810
I don't know much about guitars, but you seem like you can play quite well.

336
00:31:13.810 --> 00:31:15.760
Then, should I play Revival for you?

337
00:31:15.760 --> 00:31:17.930
Where's Sunbae Jae Hyeon?

338
00:31:17.930 --> 00:31:19.610
- Are you curious?
 - Yes.

339
00:31:19.610 --> 00:31:21.200
Give me 500 won (≈ $0.50).

340
00:31:21.200 --> 00:31:22.860
Okay.

341
00:31:26.590 --> 00:31:28.890
Did he not tell you he's preparing for the elections these days?

342
00:31:28.890 --> 00:31:31.450
Elections? Is he applying for student council president?

343
00:31:31.450 --> 00:31:33.650
Not that, chief host of student council.

344
00:31:33.650 --> 00:31:35.220
Chief Host?

345
00:31:35.220 --> 00:31:37.270
I'm the one who's good at hosting events, though.

346
00:31:37.270 --> 00:31:40.470
Ladies and gentlemen, please welcome Ji Soo Yoon.

347
00:31:40.470 --> 00:31:42.020
Is it really about being master of ceremony?

348
00:31:42.020 --> 00:31:44.950
That's right. You know how people grab the mike when demonstrating?

349
00:31:44.950 --> 00:31:47.400
So the Chief Host is a demonstrating position, originally.

350
00:31:47.400 --> 00:31:51.970
Someone who hosts the event, while caring about society, hence a chief host. 
 <i>(T/N: society and host are homonyms)</i>

351
00:31:51.970 --> 00:31:55.390
And he also has to "struggle for supplies," as well.

352
00:31:55.390 --> 00:31:57.930
"Struggle for supplies?"

353
00:32:02.510 --> 00:32:04.920
Supply struggle.

354
00:32:04.920 --> 00:32:06.880
In other words, a part-time job.

355
00:32:06.880 --> 00:32:11.490
With this, he earns money to pay for his travel expenses, his food, and campaign funds as well.

356
00:32:11.490 --> 00:32:13.460
There wouldn't be much left.

357
00:32:13.460 --> 00:32:14.750
That's carrot. <i>(in English)</i>

358
00:32:14.750 --> 00:32:15.890
A carol?

359
00:32:15.890 --> 00:32:18.490
No, carrot, "danggeun." 
 <i>(T/N: 'danggeun' means carrot, but also "that goes without saying.") </i>

360
00:32:21.200 --> 00:32:24.590
The others all laugh so hard they fall to the ground.

361
00:32:24.590 --> 00:32:28.280
But he would earn a lot more if he worked as a tutor.

362
00:32:28.280 --> 00:32:32.120
The reason why he's doing that is so apparent.

363
00:32:35.960 --> 00:32:37.630
That sunbae...

364
00:32:37.630 --> 00:32:39.290
The Invincible Hwa Jin.

365
00:32:39.290 --> 00:32:42.580
When she takes those riot squad fuzz one-on-one, she wins 100% of the time.

366
00:32:42.580 --> 00:32:45.460
Her hobby is to steal their helmets,

367
00:32:45.460 --> 00:32:47.230
so if you go to her house,

368
00:32:47.230 --> 00:32:49.720
she uses them as buckets, or to store rice in.

369
00:32:49.720 --> 00:32:51.930
She is a legendary female warrior.

370
00:32:52.990 --> 00:32:54.930
So he's working there because of her?

371
00:32:54.930 --> 00:33:00.620
No, let's do some thinking. Think.

372
00:33:00.620 --> 00:33:05.700
If he works there, he can have secret rendezvous with the others and save time going to and fro.

373
00:33:05.700 --> 00:33:08.640
It's "one hit, double blow," isn't it? <i>(in English)</i>

374
00:33:08.640 --> 00:33:09.690
What is that?

375
00:33:09.690 --> 00:33:12.490
One shot, two kills (kill two birds with one stone).

376
00:33:12.490 --> 00:33:18.250
And that purist says that tutoring rich kids is like collaborating with capitalism, so that's why he hates it.

377
00:33:18.250 --> 00:33:20.600
That tiresome punk.

378
00:33:21.400 --> 00:33:24.460
He must be so tired.

379
00:33:28.090 --> 00:33:30.810
<i>Collection of Park No Hae's Poems: Labor's Morning</i>

380
00:35:37.830 --> 00:35:41.160
Are you happy that you're the only one feeling refreshed?

381
00:35:42.260 --> 00:35:43.820
What?

382
00:35:45.450 --> 00:35:48.290
This was broken earlier.

383
00:35:49.380 --> 00:35:51.320
I can guess who came by.

384
00:35:52.130 --> 00:35:53.940
Who came by?

385
00:35:53.940 --> 00:35:56.980
You, why are you sleeping here?

386
00:35:56.980 --> 00:35:59.890
Ah, because it's hot.

387
00:35:59.890 --> 00:36:03.940
Isn't it so hot? The weather prediction says this is the hottest.

388
00:36:04.770 --> 00:36:08.310
Stop fanning me. It's not refreshing at all.

389
00:36:09.110 --> 00:36:12.980
Then don't do the part-time job at the front gate. It's so hot.

390
00:36:12.980 --> 00:36:14.900
It's this hot,

391
00:36:14.900 --> 00:36:17.550
but I'm not tired at all because of someone.

392
00:36:20.080 --> 00:36:22.420
Today really is my birthday.

393
00:36:22.910 --> 00:36:24.510
It's your birthday today?

394
00:36:24.510 --> 00:36:28.120
It's not my birthday, but it feels as good as if it was my birthday.

395
00:36:29.010 --> 00:36:30.360
When is your birthday?

396
00:36:30.360 --> 00:36:32.160
On the 29th.

397
00:36:32.670 --> 00:36:34.200
Of June.

398
00:36:34.810 --> 00:36:36.660
There isn't much time left.

399
00:36:36.660 --> 00:36:38.460
I know, right?

400
00:36:42.710 --> 00:36:45.170
<i>Nursing Ward</i>

401
00:36:52.490 --> 00:36:56.690
Where do you think this is? How dare you come here?

402
00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:01.850
Get out right now!

403
00:37:08.260 --> 00:37:10.120
You devoured her.

404
00:37:10.120 --> 00:37:11.530
If it wasn't for you.

405
00:37:11.530 --> 00:37:14.990
If it wasn't for you, she wouldn't have died!

406
00:37:14.990 --> 00:37:17.580
Get out! Get out right now!

407
00:37:17.580 --> 00:37:19.690
I said to get out!

408
00:37:19.690 --> 00:37:21.580
Why is it because of me?

409
00:37:21.580 --> 00:37:22.980
What did I do?

410
00:37:22.980 --> 00:37:26.320
What could I have done? What should I have done?!

411
00:37:27.160 --> 00:37:29.320
I know you need someone to resent.

412
00:37:29.320 --> 00:37:32.110
I know you need someone to release your anger on, but please stop now!

413
00:37:32.110 --> 00:37:34.940
It's not like she'll come back from the dead if you do this.

414
00:37:35.890 --> 00:37:37.830
I know too.

415
00:37:38.490 --> 00:37:41.320
I shouldn't have been born.

416
00:37:41.320 --> 00:37:43.920
It really should have been that way.

417
00:37:43.920 --> 00:37:47.830
If it weren't for that, everything would be fine...

418
00:37:53.890 --> 00:37:56.590
Oh my, you're like this again.

419
00:37:56.590 --> 00:37:59.980
Chief Prosecutor, it's okay.

420
00:37:59.980 --> 00:38:02.130
Please don't cry, okay?

421
00:38:02.130 --> 00:38:07.790
I bought the honey cookies that you like, so don't be mad anymore.

422
00:38:10.320 --> 00:38:15.010
Why did you suddenly start talking back? You're usually such a kind daughter.

423
00:38:26.710 --> 00:38:29.920
<i>Notice of Admission</i>
<i>Name: Yoon Ji Soo - Major: Piano </i>
<i>The person mentioned above has passed the 1993 entrance exam to Yeon Hui University.</i>

424
00:38:29.920 --> 00:38:32.000
<i>January 1993</i>

425
00:38:33.970 --> 00:38:35.370
So, what about it?

426
00:38:35.370 --> 00:38:38.880
It says Ji Soo got accepted to university.

427
00:38:38.880 --> 00:38:40.750
Is this a university?

428
00:38:40.750 --> 00:38:44.720
Banging on a piano, are you proud to attend this school?

429
00:38:44.720 --> 00:38:48.290
You are an embarrassment in front of our neighbors, so attend school quietly, as if you're dead.

430
00:38:48.900 --> 00:38:50.920
I...

431
00:38:51.750 --> 00:38:54.650
What do I have to do to be considered a person in this house?

432
00:38:55.570 --> 00:38:59.250
I was born with nothing that you are pleased with, Dad.

433
00:38:59.250 --> 00:39:02.160
Should I go back into Mom's womb?

434
00:39:02.160 --> 00:39:03.720
Ji Soo.

435
00:39:03.720 --> 00:39:05.060
Keep going, see if you dare.

436
00:39:05.060 --> 00:39:08.010
<i>Ji Yeong said she would go to law school at Seoul National University instead of me.</i>

437
00:39:08.010 --> 00:39:12.620
Then it's fine. You can hold your head high in front of your colleagues.

438
00:39:12.620 --> 00:39:15.500
<i>So you can stop now.</i>

439
00:39:15.500 --> 00:39:17.520
<i>You can let me breathe now.</i>

440
00:39:17.520 --> 00:39:20.110
<i>Because she hasn't gone yet.</i>

441
00:39:20.710 --> 00:39:23.510
<i>Ji Yeong hasn't gone to university yet.</i>

442
00:39:23.510 --> 00:39:25.440
<i>So don't even breathe.</i>

443
00:39:25.440 --> 00:39:29.860
<i>Until our Ji Yeong goes to Seoul National University.</i>

444
00:40:08.460 --> 00:40:12.500
<i>From Dad: I'm arriving in 30 minutes. Finish getting ready.</i>

445
00:40:35.750 --> 00:40:37.330
Yeong Min.

446
00:40:39.090 --> 00:40:40.910
Yeong Min. Yeong Min.

447
00:40:40.910 --> 00:40:42.730
Open the door.

448
00:40:48.550 --> 00:40:53.780
Take Joon Seo back first. I can't just leave the child at the hospital.

449
00:40:55.040 --> 00:40:56.560
Okay.

450
00:41:04.080 --> 00:41:05.950
Yeong Min.

451
00:41:11.190 --> 00:41:13.890
They say it's the flu.

452
00:41:13.890 --> 00:41:16.450
It seems like he was sick and didn't eat properly,

453
00:41:16.450 --> 00:41:19.210
so he is malnourished and dehydrated.

454
00:41:19.210 --> 00:41:21.080
Oh, I see.

455
00:41:21.080 --> 00:41:23.970
But, who are you?

456
00:41:23.970 --> 00:41:26.810
My child is his friend, in the same class as Yeong Min.

457
00:41:26.810 --> 00:41:30.910
What's your son's name? I know all of Yeong Min's friends.

458
00:41:30.910 --> 00:41:34.310
Since his father arrived, I'm going to leave.

459
00:41:34.310 --> 00:41:35.920
Goodbye.

460
00:41:40.810 --> 00:41:42.990
Son of a bitch.

461
00:42:03.820 --> 00:42:05.900
<i>Toward: Seoul - Jecheon - Yeongju</i>

462
00:43:00.130 --> 00:43:02.820
<i>Emergency Medical Center</i>

463
00:43:14.490 --> 00:43:18.150
How did you take care of him, that he would faint over the mere flu?

464
00:43:18.150 --> 00:43:21.270
If you're going to be like this, I have no choice but to take back custody.

465
00:43:21.270 --> 00:43:24.100
Try and take it, I'll rip you apart.

466
00:43:25.310 --> 00:43:26.910
Such incredible maternal instinct.

467
00:43:26.910 --> 00:43:29.200
But why did you take the father away from your son?

468
00:43:29.200 --> 00:43:31.900
You can't take Yeong Min, I'm going to take him.

469
00:43:31.900 --> 00:43:35.750
I'm sorry, but my mother is coming here.

470
00:43:58.850 --> 00:44:00.780
Son.

471
00:44:04.760 --> 00:44:07.090
Son, have you been well?

472
00:44:07.090 --> 00:44:08.550
Yes.

473
00:44:09.310 --> 00:44:13.780
You're so curt. As if anyone would think you're not your father's son.

474
00:44:15.630 --> 00:44:17.090
Where's your dad?

475
00:44:17.090 --> 00:44:19.560
- He's probably at school. 
 - Why?

476
00:44:19.560 --> 00:44:21.440
That punk fainted.

477
00:44:21.440 --> 00:44:22.840
That punk?

478
00:44:22.840 --> 00:44:26.040
The one who threw the chair at me.

479
00:44:32.450 --> 00:44:38.180
♫ <i>Don't say anything</i> ♫

480
00:44:39.360 --> 00:44:45.760
♫ <i>if it's about the past</i> ♫

481
00:44:45.760 --> 00:44:51.310
♫ <i>In all our many stories</i> ♫

482
00:44:52.620 --> 00:44:59.590
♫ <i>there are so many misunderstandings</i> ♫

483
00:45:01.540 --> 00:45:08.530
♫ <i>Don't ask me </i> ♫

484
00:45:08.530 --> 00:45:14.970
♫ <i>if it's about the past</i> ♫

485
00:45:14.970 --> 00:45:21.440
♫ <i>Whatever the answer is</i> ♫

486
00:45:21.440 --> 00:45:28.220
♫ <i>I can’t tell you the truth</i> ♫

487
00:45:28.220 --> 00:45:34.140
♫ <i>Just bury them in your heart</i> ♫

488
00:45:34.140 --> 00:45:40.690
♫ <i>Words you wanted to say</i> ♫

489
00:45:40.690 --> 00:45:42.990
Please follow that bus.

490
00:45:48.760 --> 00:45:54.910
♫ <i>Even the scattered memories</i> ♫

491
00:45:54.910 --> 00:46:01.640
♫ <i>We’ll see each other again</i> ♫

492
00:46:01.640 --> 00:46:08.520
♫ <i>Give me a hug, then</i> ♫

493
00:46:08.520 --> 00:46:13.910
♫ <i>Though I couldn't bring myself to do it today.</i> ♫

494
00:46:13.910 --> 00:46:16.170
Sleep well, Ji Soo.

495
00:46:16.170 --> 00:46:22.930
♫ <i>Do that instead of saying you're sorry.</i> ♫

496
00:46:28.120 --> 00:46:32.440
It's because of me, right?

497
00:46:32.440 --> 00:46:35.640
The reason why you weren't happy all this time.

498
00:46:36.480 --> 00:46:40.210
- Isn't it because you chose me? 
 - Seo Gyeong...

499
00:46:40.210 --> 00:46:44.950
I always said this to my dad.

500
00:46:44.950 --> 00:46:50.000
That you were the best decision of my life.

501
00:46:50.000 --> 00:46:54.360
I'm thankful for that, so I'm doing my best.

502
00:46:55.670 --> 00:47:02.430
You were the best for me, but to you, I was the best you could do.

503
00:47:02.430 --> 00:47:04.710
- Seo Gyeong.
 - Stop talking.

504
00:47:04.710 --> 00:47:09.540
I understand everything, with the word "thankful."

505
00:47:16.920 --> 00:47:18.890
<i>Hyeong Seong</i>

506
00:47:18.890 --> 00:47:21.810
- She is working at the hotel. 
 - What work is she doing?

507
00:47:21.810 --> 00:47:24.220
She plays the piano in the lounge.

508
00:47:24.220 --> 00:47:27.900
- Jae Hyeon goes there often. 
 - Yes.

509
00:47:27.900 --> 00:47:31.270
By chance, could she have been a gold digger from the start?

510
00:47:31.270 --> 00:47:36.120
She started working a year ago, which was when the vice president was incarcerated.

511
00:47:36.120 --> 00:47:39.940
Who knows? Maybe she visited him in prison.

512
00:47:39.940 --> 00:47:44.390
But something special that she does performs with a  mask on her face.

513
00:47:44.390 --> 00:47:46.240
Really?

514
00:47:49.120 --> 00:47:52.170
So she doesn't want her face to become known, huh?

515
00:47:54.120 --> 00:47:58.320
I need to put her in her place.

516
00:47:58.320 --> 00:48:02.510
- Do you have time on Friday evening? 
 - Why?

517
00:48:02.510 --> 00:48:05.160
There is going to be a private party in a suite room that day.

518
00:48:05.160 --> 00:48:10.790
They asked for a piano performance, from you specifically.

519
00:48:12.400 --> 00:48:14.480
- From me? 
 - Yes.

520
00:48:14.480 --> 00:48:18.130
They asked specifically for the person who plays with a mask on.

521
00:48:18.130 --> 00:48:22.430
- They said they like your performance the best. 
 - Who ist it?

522
00:48:22.430 --> 00:48:25.360
A VVVIP client.

523
00:48:25.360 --> 00:48:28.140
They said you'll find out who they are if you come that day.

524
00:48:28.140 --> 00:48:32.420
The pay is twice the usual amount.

525
00:48:42.520 --> 00:48:46.210
Since it's a party for this brand, they asked you to wear this.

526
00:48:46.210 --> 00:48:48.160
They said you can just return it when it ends.

527
00:48:48.160 --> 00:48:50.870
Such an expensive item.

528
00:48:51.660 --> 00:48:53.560
What do I do if something bad happens to it.

529
00:48:53.560 --> 00:48:56.370
Oh, I'm sure nothing will happen.

530
00:49:06.300 --> 00:49:08.100
You're going to come, right?

531
00:49:08.100 --> 00:49:09.900
No.

532
00:49:09.900 --> 00:49:12.380
It's a command from your boss (me).

533
00:49:12.380 --> 00:49:15.760
It's not just a party, but a showcase for our brand.

534
00:49:15.760 --> 00:49:16.950
I know that I don't have to go.

535
00:49:16.950 --> 00:49:20.150
Things such as having influencers taking pictures to upload it onto their SNS,

536
00:49:20.150 --> 00:49:23.010
global top brands do all those things too.

537
00:49:23.010 --> 00:49:28.040
Does it make sense for the president to go to this event, but for the vice president not to?

538
00:49:28.040 --> 00:49:29.850
Seo Gyeong.

539
00:49:30.870 --> 00:49:32.910
Can you not even do this much for me?

540
00:49:32.910 --> 00:49:35.460
You can spend a whole day at the ER for someone else's son,

541
00:49:35.460 --> 00:49:38.580
but you can't spend just two hours for your wife.

542
00:49:38.580 --> 00:49:42.650
Is that what you call doing your best?

543
00:49:43.950 --> 00:49:46.970
Even if I'm not smart, my intuition is good.

544
00:49:48.170 --> 00:49:53.670
I said that I love you, how can you reply that you're thankful?

545
00:49:53.670 --> 00:49:56.370
And why didn't you say you're sorry?

546
00:49:59.210 --> 00:50:03.400
Live the rest of your life apologizing to me.

547
00:51:07.500 --> 00:51:09.480
- Oh my, it's been a long time. 
 - Hello.

548
00:51:09.480 --> 00:51:12.250
- It has been a long time, hasn't it? 
 - Thank you for coming.

549
00:51:14.080 --> 00:51:16.880
Jae Hyeon, where are you?

550
00:51:18.470 --> 00:51:20.970
Okay, come quickly.

551
00:51:29.740 --> 00:51:32.080
Drink this as you perform.

552
00:51:34.400 --> 00:51:37.480
You can't put the drink here. Oh no!

553
00:51:43.280 --> 00:51:45.760
Oh no, are you okay? Oh no, what do we do?

554
00:52:04.300 --> 00:52:06.140
Are you okay?

555
00:52:06.140 --> 00:52:08.370
Please wait a moment.

556
00:52:18.000 --> 00:52:22.530
Please continue to perform. The music can't stop.

557
00:52:22.530 --> 00:52:26.430
The dress costs several times more than your pay,

558
00:52:26.430 --> 00:52:30.020
so I'll just give you the dress.

559
00:52:30.020 --> 00:52:33.590
Instead, I wish you could take off your mask.

560
00:52:34.330 --> 00:52:40.060
Since you spilled red wine, of all things, it looks a bit grotesque.

561
00:52:43.280 --> 00:52:45.920
<i>September, 1994</i>

562
00:52:54.910 --> 00:52:59.800
- Oh, girl. You look disgustingly pretty. 
 - Right?

563
00:52:59.800 --> 00:53:02.210
Thank you.

564
00:53:02.210 --> 00:53:04.860
- Where are your parents? 
- I didn't ask them to come.

565
00:53:04.860 --> 00:53:07.960
- Why? 
- Because this is nothing big.

566
00:53:07.960 --> 00:53:09.800
What do you mean nothing big?

567
00:53:09.800 --> 00:53:12.620
You are performing after scoring first at this difficult competition.

568
00:53:12.620 --> 00:53:14.380
They wouldn't have come even if I asked them to.

569
00:53:14.380 --> 00:53:15.410
No way.

570
00:53:15.410 --> 00:53:18.340
There isn't much time left until Ji Yeong's college entrance exams.

571
00:53:18.340 --> 00:53:23.990
Seriously, they're quite amazing. What about him?

572
00:53:23.990 --> 00:53:26.540
He said he'll come after the rally.

573
00:53:26.540 --> 00:53:28.930
Does the world collapse if he misses one rally?

574
00:53:28.930 --> 00:53:30.720
They said it's a rally that won't work without him.

575
00:53:30.720 --> 00:53:32.690
Those damned rallies.

576
00:53:32.690 --> 00:53:36.030
He can't even protect his own girlfriend. How does he think he can protect the world?

577
00:53:36.030 --> 00:53:40.090
A world he protects that way must be so beautiful. What a joke!

578
00:53:40.090 --> 00:53:43.200
Oh, this makes me so angry.

579
00:53:43.200 --> 00:53:45.770
Stop smiling.

580
00:54:15.050 --> 00:54:16.830
Sorry.

581
00:54:16.830 --> 00:54:18.910
It's okay.

582
00:54:20.570 --> 00:54:22.720
- Where's your family? 
 - Ah...

583
00:54:22.720 --> 00:54:24.650
That question again.

584
00:54:24.650 --> 00:54:27.020
Ji Soo.

585
00:54:27.020 --> 00:54:29.180
I didn't ask them to come.

586
00:54:29.180 --> 00:54:30.830
Why?

587
00:54:35.130 --> 00:54:38.290
Because I won't see them in the future anymore.

588
00:54:38.290 --> 00:54:40.200
What are you saying?

589
00:54:41.110 --> 00:54:43.980
You taught me, Sunbae.

590
00:54:58.870 --> 00:55:04.640
To not let anyone treat me poorly.

591
00:55:10.510 --> 00:55:16.750
Because I am a very precious child of God.

592
00:55:28.200 --> 00:55:30.790
I will not perform.

593
00:55:30.790 --> 00:55:35.030
Why? Because your face has been revealed?

594
00:55:35.030 --> 00:55:38.150
No, because this is a pearl necklace hung around a swine's neck.

595
00:55:38.150 --> 00:55:39.880
What?

596
00:55:39.880 --> 00:55:43.210
I'm saying that it's a waste of my luxurious performance to perform at such a tacky party

597
00:55:43.210 --> 00:55:46.470
that is only about showing off money. 
 <i>(T/N: she switched to informal speech)</i>

598
00:55:53.990 --> 00:55:56.620
I'll be the one to pay for this dress. 
 <i>(T/N: informal speech)</i>

599
00:56:04.410 --> 00:56:07.050
<i>I'm not going to take it anymore.</i>

600
00:56:07.050 --> 00:56:09.620
<i>Getting hit by my father.</i>

601
00:56:12.180 --> 00:56:15.930
<i>Why did you get hit?</i>

602
00:56:15.930 --> 00:56:20.090
<i>I got caught listening to pop music.</i>

603
00:56:20.090 --> 00:56:23.450
<i>He said that playing the piano is already laughable, and now I'm listening to entertainers' music.</i>

604
00:56:23.450 --> 00:56:26.420
<i>So he got mad and threw the radio.</i>

605
00:56:31.020 --> 00:56:32.920
Sunbae.

606
00:56:36.440 --> 00:56:39.210
I want to see the ocean.

607
00:57:14.830 --> 00:57:16.740
<i>Where do you think this is?</i>

608
00:57:16.740 --> 00:57:19.420
<i>How dare you come here?</i>

609
00:57:19.420 --> 00:57:21.650
<i>You devoured her.</i>

610
00:57:21.650 --> 00:57:24.010
<i> If it wasn't for you. </i>

611
00:57:24.010 --> 00:57:27.410
<i>If it wasn't for you, she wouldn't have died!</i>

612
00:57:27.410 --> 00:57:29.960
<i>Get out! Get out right now!</i>

613
00:57:29.960 --> 00:57:32.320
<i>I said to get out!</i>

614
00:58:26.520 --> 00:58:29.210
I'm sorry, Ji Soo.

615
00:58:34.250 --> 00:58:36.550
I'm sorry.

616
00:58:39.990 --> 00:58:41.920
Sunbae.

617
00:58:46.220 --> 00:58:49.390
Why did I have to be the one to survive?

618
00:58:52.730 --> 00:58:56.120
To be alive is a sin and a debt.

619
00:58:57.190 --> 00:59:00.610
So I can't ever be happy

620
00:59:00.610 --> 00:59:03.380
and I can't ever complain.

621
00:59:04.630 --> 00:59:08.320
Even if I live every day not having the time to sit down,

622
00:59:11.120 --> 00:59:14.230
be it the price of my sin or my debt,

623
00:59:15.870 --> 00:59:18.960
none of it becomes any smaller.

624
00:59:21.170 --> 00:59:23.200
Now,

625
00:59:27.090 --> 00:59:29.550
I really want to rest.

626
00:59:32.760 --> 00:59:35.170
I want to let everything go.

627
01:00:03.010 --> 01:00:05.680
<i>It's so romantic.</i>

628
01:00:05.680 --> 01:00:07.910
- Is it your first time riding a train? 
 - Yes.

629
01:00:07.910 --> 01:00:10.930
<i>But are we not going to eat eggs? What about soda?</i>

630
01:00:10.930 --> 01:00:14.740
They sell boxed meals while going back and forth with a cart here, right?

631
01:00:14.740 --> 01:00:21.500
♫ <i>Someday, we'll probably</i> ♫

632
01:00:21.500 --> 01:00:26.340
♫ <i>remember, right?</i> ♫

633
01:00:27.720 --> 01:00:31.890
♫ <i>In another memory </i> ♫

634
01:00:31.890 --> 01:00:40.630
♫ <i>the promise we hid away</i> ♫

635
01:00:41.480 --> 01:00:48.270
♫ <i>We were drunk on an exciting love at the time, with everything passing us by</i> ♫

636
01:00:48.270 --> 01:00:55.520
♫ <i> It must feel cold and lonely because those insignificant days were inelegant </i> ♫

637
01:00:55.520 --> 01:01:01.680
♫ <i>But it suddenly comes, the longing that is called "you"</i> ♫

638
01:01:01.680 --> 01:01:09.010
♫ <i>If we can go back to that time, I would tell you everything</i> ♫

639
01:01:09.010 --> 01:01:16.140
♫ <i>To that day, to that time, if we could go back</i> ♫

640
01:01:16.140 --> 01:01:22.900
♫ <i>I could convey it all with just one embrace</i> ♫

641
01:01:22.900 --> 01:01:30.110
♫ <i>If that day, if that time, even once it passes</i> ♫

642
01:01:30.110 --> 01:01:38.210
♫ <i>Then it becomes tomorrow, no longer a memory</i> ♫

643
01:01:48.460 --> 01:01:50.580
I...

644
01:01:51.450 --> 01:01:57.480
I think that to those who survived, there is a reason for their living.

645
01:02:00.070 --> 01:02:03.900
That it's because there are things that only you can do in this world.

646
01:02:08.860 --> 01:02:15.200
So you being alive may be a blessing to us.

647
01:02:17.480 --> 01:02:21.540
So Ji Soo, you can do it all.

648
01:02:22.860 --> 01:02:27.650
You can rest, you can cry.

649
01:02:27.650 --> 01:02:33.340
If you're having a hard time, you don't have to grit your teeth and endure it.

650
01:02:35.690 --> 01:02:38.580
Because I'll be by your side.

651
01:02:52.160 --> 01:02:55.130
Why would you be by my side?

652
01:02:55.130 --> 01:02:59.880
I should be in my place, and you should be in your place.

653
01:02:59.880 --> 01:03:01.600
That's right.

654
01:03:03.070 --> 01:03:05.750
Anyone would know that this was just an escape.

655
01:03:06.520 --> 01:03:12.390
And even for a first love, we cannot justify an inappropriate relationship.

656
01:03:12.390 --> 01:03:18.280
But why can't I turn away from you?

657
01:03:19.710 --> 01:03:23.050
Why can't I leave us in my memories?

658
01:03:25.290 --> 01:03:27.870
I kept thinking about it.

659
01:03:29.670 --> 01:03:32.640
And I found that the answer was in our past.

660
01:03:34.960 --> 01:03:36.900
You said this.

661
01:03:37.560 --> 01:03:39.570
Your belief,

662
01:03:41.520 --> 01:03:44.230
your world is me.

663
01:03:49.780 --> 01:03:53.100
There was something I couldn't say at the time.

664
01:03:56.790 --> 01:03:59.820
To me, you were my dream.

665
01:04:04.590 --> 01:04:08.220
Now that I'm again facing the dream I had lost,

666
01:04:12.280 --> 01:04:14.410
I found myself unable to throw it away

667
01:04:17.220 --> 01:04:19.910
nor run away.

668
01:04:26.060 --> 01:04:28.370
Because that's what a dream is.

669
01:04:42.500 --> 01:04:44.750
Because it's a dream.

670
01:04:51.170 --> 01:04:53.760
Because you'll wake up from it soon.

671
01:05:12.860 --> 01:05:22.310
♫ <i>Spring is blossoming in our hearts</i> ♫

672
01:05:22.310 --> 01:05:28.920
♫ <i>My fluttering heart waits for you</i> ♫

673
01:05:28.920 --> 01:05:34.680
♫ <i>Our fluttering gazes</i> ♫


675
01:05:38.950 --> 01:05:41.540
<i>When My Love Blooms -  Preview</i>

676
01:05:41.540 --> 01:05:46.230
<i>Just a dream. Because it's all a dream.</i>

677
01:05:46.230 --> 01:05:50.080
<i>You do know, don't you? That I've been with another man, too?</i>

678
01:05:50.080 --> 01:05:52.370
<i>So don't be so serious about it.</i>

679
01:05:52.370 --> 01:05:58.600
<i>They say that there are people who meet again in the end, no matter how.</i>

680
01:05:58.600 --> 01:06:00.590
<i>That black car behind us? How long has it been following us?</i>

681
01:06:00.590 --> 01:06:05.300
<i>The thing I'm most afraid of, is that person being ruined because of me.</i>

682
01:06:05.300 --> 01:06:08.060
<i>I decided to avoid the thing I was most afraid of.</i>

683
01:06:08.060 --> 01:06:13.130
♫ <i>Our hearts are colored with autumn</i> ♫

